ðŸ“‚ File Sharing with Samba

Set up Samba for network file sharing across devices.

Installation
sudo apt install samba -y

Configuration

Edit Samba config:

sudo nano /etc/samba/smb.conf


Add this share:

[SharedFiles]
   path = /srv/shared
   browsable = yes
   writable = yes
   guest ok = no
   read only = no


Create shared folder and set permissions:

sudo mkdir -p /srv/shared
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /srv/shared


Add a Samba user:

sudo smbpasswd -a $USER


Restart Samba:

sudo systemctl restart smbd

Access

From Windows: \\<server-ip>\SharedFiles

From Linux: smb://<server-ip>/SharedFiles
